1
00:00:26,040 --> 00:00:28,370
This make-up exam is only 90 minutes long.

2
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:30,760
Since there aren't many people taking the make-up exam,

3
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,439
after you hand in your papers later,

4
00:00:32,439 --> 00:00:34,160
I will grade them immediately.

5
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:36,640
Especially for Yin Zixi and Wen Lingli.

6
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:39,480
This make-up exam directly determines

7
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:40,600
which of you will be the spokesperson.

8
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,200
This is your chance to prove yourselves again.

9
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:46,540
Pass these out.

10
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:05,960
Zixi.

11
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,400
Actually, that answer sheet...

12
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,760
Should I call her Zixi,

13
00:01:13,039 --> 00:01:14,520
or Xiaoxi?

14
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,520
What do you think, Hao?

15
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,160
Me? I have no time.

16
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:22,480
Xiaoxi, actually the answers to that test paper...

17
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,680
That's not right either.

18
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,860
I should ask her how she did on the test first.

19
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:29,640
Boss.

20
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:31,920
It seems we have a situation.

21
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,280
Teacher.

22
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,560
Hmm, so fast?

23
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:41,210
Yeah.

24
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:44,780
You don't even know how to keep a low profile when cheating.

25
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:50,520
Hey.

26
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,970
Everyone is so fast.

27
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,160
Okay.

28
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,320
Wen Lingli.

29
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:09,080
I didn't give you these answers.

30
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,960
The score for these answers is exactly 60, a passing grade.

31
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,680
Is that so?

32
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,840
I knew there was something wrong with this test paper.

33
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,800
Yin Zixi,

34
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,360
congratulations.

35
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,040
Yin Zixi.

36
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:22,680
What?

37
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,160
She cheated?

38
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:25,880
You're the one who cheated, right?

39
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,760
Wait,

40
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:27,850
what's going on?

41
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,250
I don't accept this.

42
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,880
She finished so quickly,

43
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,440
how could she score so high?

44
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,800
It is a bit strange.

45
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,640
How about this?

46
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,560
I'll come up with a question on the spot.

47
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,000
Whoever answers it correctly

48
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,460
will be the spokesperson.

49
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,520
What does the authenticity of news

50
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,640
refer to?

51
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,800
Yes.

52
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,040
The authenticity of news

53
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,480
means that in a news report,

54
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,360
every fact

55
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,079
must be objectively true.

56
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,280
Shown in the news report,

57
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,280
the time, place,

58
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,440
people, events, causes,

59
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,560
and processes must all stand up to verification.

60
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,160
The basic point of authenticity

61
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,360
is that in a news report,

62
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,200
every fact

63
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,160
must match the objective facts.

64
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:10,400
Correct.

65
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,330
You have no objections now, right?

66
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,400
Now please tell me,

67
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,000
what's this about cheating?

68
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:27,880
Zixi, actually, those answers...

69
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,520
Xiaoxi.

70
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,160
Actually...

71
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Xiaoxi.

72
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,600
Zixi.

73
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,880
You finished the exam so quickly.

74
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,800
Yeah, easier than expected.

75
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,320
Yang Qian said you came looking for me a few times.

76
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,600
Yeah, I did.

77
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,840
You argued with the senior last time.

78
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,440
I was a bit worried about you.

79
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,200
I was just a bit hot-headed at the time.

80
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,200
Thank you.

81
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,520
If there's nothing else, I'll be going now.

82
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,880
Oh, okay.

83
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,920
Bye.

84
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,640
Bye.

85
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,600
Yin Zixi.

86
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,000
Congratulations.

87
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:14,200
Oh, thanks. Bye.

88
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,160
Bye.

89
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,760
Senior, I'm done with my exams.

90
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:52,040
Cheers to passing.

91
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,720
A midnight snack is awesome.

92
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,080
Finally, I don't have to eat canteen food.

93
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,320
You should have told me earlier.

94
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,360
I haven't taken you to the snack street in the back yet.

95
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,160
Is there one?

96
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,480
I walked a long way

97
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,160
to find this fried chicken place.

98
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,040
Then you went the wrong way.

99
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,960
These roads have changed so much.

100
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,040
I really couldn't recognize them.

101
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:15,120
Anyway, it's not like you've been bad with directions for just a day or two.

102
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,050
What do you mean?

103
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:19,840
Aren't you going to be busy starting your livestream business?

104
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,480
How do you plan to start?

105
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:22,640
Yeah.

106
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:25,280
Have you seen a restaurant called Mujing?

107
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,600
It's right behind the snack street.

108
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,000
But I advise you not to go.

109
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,080
Why?

110
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,760
That place is far,

111
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,000
and their business hours are irregular.

112
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,120
I went twice, and it was closed both times.

113
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,360
Oh.

114
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,040
Is Uncle He from 2016

115
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,400
in Mujing Restaurant?

116
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,480
Uncle He.

117
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,240
I didn't see that document.

118
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,640
I might have left it at my shop.

119
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,840
Just come over and pick it up.

120
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:52,480
Okay.

121
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,400
Where is the shop?

122
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,000
Mujing Restaurant. I'll text it to you.

123
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,440
Okay.

124
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,080
Finally found it.

125
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:14,800
Welcome.

126
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,400
Senior.

127
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,560
Yin Zixi.

128
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,080
Senior.

129
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,040
Sit down.

130
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,690
You promised to let me come.

131
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,920
Then congratulations

132
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,050
on passing the exam.

133
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,800
I wanted to celebrate with you after the exam,

134
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,320
but you left too fast.

135
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,600
I haven't been back to the shop for a few days.

136
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,480
Why are you working part-time here?

137
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,040
This shop is run by my relative.

138
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,840
It's kind of

139
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,300
a work-study program.

140
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,280
Relative?

141
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:46,760
Senior.

142
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,480
Then do you know Uncle He Kang?

143
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,000
Uncle He.

144
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,320
Why did you open the door so early?

145
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,440
Who is it?

146
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,360
Yufan.

147
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,680
You brought your girlfriend here

148
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,140
without telling me first.

149
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,170
No, Uncle He.

150
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,520
You misunderstood.

151
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,280
It's like this.

152
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,480
Take your girlfriend out for a few days.

153
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,480
She really isn't my girlfriend.

154
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,480
And I haven't been back to the restaurant for days.

155
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,440
It's fine.

156
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,520
My shop doesn't need you either.

157
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,720
Uncle He.

158
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:19,020
The restaurant is opening soon at 11.

159
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,920
It's changed to 12 now.

160
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:24,370
Uncle He.

161
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,560
I really won't leave

162
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,920
unless you help me get back to the group headquarters.

163
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,850
Here we go again.

164
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,000
If I don't find out the truth,

165
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,000
I won't accept it.

166
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:35,680
You win some and you lose some in business competition.

167
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,760
The truth doesn't change the ending.

168
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,440
Then I need to figure out exactly where I lost.

169
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,640
You young people,

170
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,080
why are you so stubborn?

171
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,520
It's getting late.

172
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,780
I have an appointment.

173
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,340
You have no appointments.

174
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,240
I checked your schedule this morning.

175
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,720
Then I'll go out for a walk.

176
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,760
Mr. He.

177
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,080
The restaurant is about to open.

178
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,740
We don't have any other staff.

179
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,600
Yin Zixi?

180
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,160
Hello, Mr. He.

181
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,320
The thing is,

182
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,120
I know you are well-connected,

183
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:10,840
so I...

184
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:11,560
Zixi.

185
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,480
I heard from Yufan

186
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:15,920
that he spent the last two days tutoring you.

187
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,040
It caused our shop a lot of losses.

188
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,320
I...

189
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,280
It's a good thing for young people to love learning.

190
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,280
How about this?

191
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,360
If you have any other lessons to catch up on,

192
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,920
do it all at once.

193
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,480
Huh?

194
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,000
I'll go talk to Yufan.

195
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:31,960
No.

196
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,760
Uncle He,

197
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,720
I want to ask for your help.

198
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:35,720
I...

199
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:40,640
I want to find a women's clothing company

200
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,880
shifting from export

201
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,360
to domestic sales.

202
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,480
The closer to school,

203
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,480
the better.

204
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,680
I want to start a business on campus

205
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,040
and do live streaming.

206
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,920
It's quite a hassle to find one.

207
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:53,680
Yes.

208
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:54,640
But

209
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,570
I won't let you help me for nothing.

210
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:59,160
I have prepared three compensation plans:

211
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,520
profit sharing,

212
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,520
regular compensation, and a lump-sum payment.

213
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,720
After finding one,

214
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,440
how do you plan to negotiate?

215
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,880
I have thought of a few plans for this too.

216
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,740
How about this?

217
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:09,880
Once I find one,

218
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,480
I will connect you directly.

219
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:12,840
Really?

220
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,080
Thank you, Uncle.

221
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,200
You are Yufan's friend.

222
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,180
It's only right for me to help you.

223
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,520
It's just...

224
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,440
Alas.

225
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,560
There is a problem now.

226
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,360
What's wrong?

227
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,280
Senior.

228
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:30,920
Are you done talking?

229
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,600
Why did you trap Uncle He?

230
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,240
I...

231
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,680
I had no choice.

232
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,120
I hope to move him with my sincerity.

233
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,680
My dad was framed.

234
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,730
I need him to help me find the truth.

235
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,600
Because of this,

236
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,560
my mom was so heartbroken

237
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,160
that she got sick and was hospitalized.

238
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:55,840
Hey.

239
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,480
She was clearly hospitalized for appendicitis surgery.

240
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,240
That was also because emotional distress

241
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,700
caused the appendicitis.

242
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,160
Asking you to come back to study,

243
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,720
was what your dad instructed me to do.

244
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,160
You are still a student.

245
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,720
At the end of the day,

246
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,520
you just don't believe me.

247
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,240
Senior,

248
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,050
don't make things difficult for Uncle He.

249
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,280
Tell you what.

250
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,200
I know you're not in the mood to study.

251
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,520
Go start a business.

252
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,520
What?

253
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,040
Zixi has a project here.

254
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,320
If you can help her earn 300,000,

255
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:26,340
I'll help you return to the group.

256
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,560
300,000?

257
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:29,360
What?

258
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:31,560
If you can't even earn this little money,

259
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,620
do you still want to return to the group to help your dad?

260
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,560
Assistant Casting Director Xi Chongjing

261
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:51,440
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

262
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,400
Yi Mingle

263
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,280
Yitong
